Class ExtensionWithContext<V extends Variable<V,T>,T extends Value<V,T>,C extends AssignmentContext>

  • Type Parameters:

    All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DistanceConflict, MacPropagation, MacRevised, SearchIntensification, StudentQuality, TimeOverlapsCounter

    public abstract class ExtensionWithContext<V extends Variable<V,T>,T extends Value<V,T>,C extends AssignmentContext>
extends Extension<V,T>
implements HasAssignmentContext<V,T,C>, CanHoldContext
    An extension with an assignment context. In order to be able to hold multiple assignments in memory it is desired for all the assignment dependent data an extension may need (to effectively enumerate its objectives), to store these data in a separate class (implementing the AssignmentContext interface). This context is created by calling HasAssignmentContext.createAssignmentContext(Assignment) and accessed by ConstraintWithContext.getContext(Assignment).
    Version:
    IFS 1.3 (Iterative Forward Search)
